        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:48AM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 447 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Murphy, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Andrews, Murphy, Nantahala Lake, Tusquitee, Violet, Topton, Hiawasse
Dam, Marble, and Unaka.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
